        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:25PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mountain Grove, or 9 miles northwest of Warm Springs. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mountain Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
